<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=969782244851></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f969782244851><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=969782244851>RE: Raising High Pass Faction</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=969782244851#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Sep 24th 3:57 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Faction question?  Heh, as an iksar monk I know these damn things like the back of my hand.  <br><br>First off, someone was mentioning hitting a point where they only got the negative faction.  Try letting the faction you are hunting kill you once.  Voila!  You will be able to start gaining faction again!  Why?  Well, the best explanation I have is that your faction bottoms out with the group at a certain point, and after they kill you they decide they don't hate you as much, so you go back to getting faction.  Laugh all you want, I have verified it four times in Blackburrow personally, and others places, as well.  Is it stupid?  Heh, what do you expect on a game where the guard who looks on you 'kindly' will help the opposing faction kill you?  Heh!<br><br>Oh, back to the point.  The bank in High Pass has a little catch.  There's a bard guilder that is sometimes near it.  Fun, huh?  That bard guilder probably isn't gonna be friendly with you, and I know it's faction has ZERO to do with the rest of highpass (go to Mistmoore to gain bard faction), so it'll be happy to KOS you most of the time.  And naturally those guards who might adore you to death will help the bard kill you, even though you did nothing and the bard attacked first.  Did I mention faction is lame and stupid?  Heh.<br><br>The key to making it all work with minimal suicides is to get your charisma sky-high.  It raises the bonus from factions and lower the negative faction hits, meaning you don't have to let a gnoll or orc kill you to gain faction again (don't forget that both gnolls and orcs grant pluses to high pass faction).  I recommend golden cat's eye agate bracelets (+7 charm a piece) and a trusty crude stein (+15 charm).  Not all that bad, since you should be able to get it all for no more than 60pp.<br><br><br>Elleandra on Nameless and Solusek Ro<br>25th Monk and 1st Necro (woowoo, finally a real class, eh?)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
