	   <tr><td colspan=2>Erudite Necromancer - Verant's Vision.<br><br>Next time you are on, do a /who all dark elf necro.  You will ALWAYS get too many returns.  That is because, like the other elf races, the Teir Dal are overplayed, and especially encromancers.  I have never seen double digit erudite necros on.  The high intel is great, and the no night vision is a bummer.  To fix that, you are almost stuck until you get your deadeye spell, or get a harvester.  Check out the Erudite section for newbie guides.  Other necro hunting grounds are the same as for pther races, but you are not KOS in as many cities.  However, you will need invis to get through Qeynos before you kill 1000 gnolls in BB and can sell.  This is kind of a bummer, since the Shrine of bertoxx somehow went dubious to me, and I couldnt buy food!  You will need these guys during your early levels, so don't do quests that hurt your Bloodsabres faction.  Kill gnolls and do the gnoll teeth quest in Qeynos to get in good with the locals.<br>And why do I think that Verant wanted necros to be Erudites?  Take a look at all the necromancers in the necro quest armor (shadowbound / robe of enshroudment with harvester).  Death Incarnate.  You get more comments on your appearance than Pally's do with Soulfire.  <br>&nbsp;<br>Warven Soulwraith<br>Eci Server</td></tr>
