	   <tr><td colspan=2>Are you joking me? There is hardly any way to play an erudite necro. Plus, they have no dex. I say start with a gnome or a darkie. Both good choices. Dump most of your points into int, and a few into dex. Then start hunting in your newbie zone. For a gnome necro(what I play): Hunt in your newbie area until level 2 or 3. Then head to the mills, or wherever. DO NOT SUMMON YOUR FIRST LEVEL PET. He will eat all your EXP. Just ask around for places to hunt. After you get to level 4, buy all your spells, and either get some buffs, or group and hit the kobold camps. Then at level 6 or 7 head to crush bone. At level 8, get Ward undead first, its your best spell this level, and head over to A. The dragon bones B. The gears and after you hit level 9 or 10 C. Chessboard in butcherblok. You will need to group. You are on your own from there, and I am off to play, my patch just finished :P. Sorry if my post was a bit long, or a bit wierd sounding, its a bit rushed :P<br><br><br>~Winspus the Necro <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
