	   <tr><td colspan=2>You mention you do not wish to rely on a weapon.<br><br>You had better change your mind. For the first few levels - say to 16th or so - sharing damage with your pet is an essential tactic. The pet can tank, but use the F1 twice method to target it and check its health, or have a /pet report health hotkey set up. If it gets low, move in and take the hits.<br><br>The key to leveling at this level is speed. It's not avoiding death, that will happen, but it is getting back up, back to your corpse, and murdering as many low level monsters as quick as you possibly can, non stop.<br><br>You can kill decaying skeletons and keep the bone chips. Dont hand them in for xp. Wait for someone like me to come to Nektulos and /auction 'buying bonechips 10pp per stack' and sell them. I and many other high level necros will buy as many as you have. I buy a whole pack ata time. This kind of money at your level will buy all your spells to level 12 after the first big sale, buy you all over cloth, and let you afford a decent weapon for your level, like a runed totem staff which is great for as long as you use a weapon to fight with for a non twink.<br><br>You should be able to make level 4 in hours, and kill some harder mobs. Avoid the pointless full groups camping orcs in east commons and making a sliver of xp per hour. When you get to level 6 ish you can be killing full skeletons with care, and easily by 8th. At 8th you can go and kill caimen in oasis with a partner, and be soloing there by 12th.<br><br>Never group with more people than you need to to get a job done, except for fun and company, and learning to group with your class. <br><br>By 16th level leave oasis and go and hunt in lake rathe killing aviak guards.<br><br>Necros are an excellent (if misunderstood) class, and can be great fun to play both solo and in groups.<br><br>Nocturne Shadowfyre<br>56 Defiler/50 Ranger/46 Monk<br>Midnight Sojourn<br>Erolissi Marr<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td><