<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9666868066178></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9666868066178><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=9666868066178>splitting 2 mobs</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=9666868066178#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 19th 8:06 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>IF you have to split 2 mobs, use screaming terror, or fear to get rid of one of them, then back away from the spawn point out of aggro range, and set your pet on the second target.<br>Do this quickly and feign death.<br>Stay feigned until your terror or fear spell has worn off (on wearing off it aggros mob), and the first mob will forget about you, you can stand up and kill the mob on your pet.<br>Another way, is to darkness one of the mobs, run off with both chasing you, and feign until the darkness wears off.  The darknessed mob will usually not begin to return to spawn point until after the dot wears off, while the other mob will usually wander back 10 seconds or so after you feign.<br>Make sure your pet is left in a safe area, away from the path you are leading the mobs on, and when darkness wears off, get up asap--your pet suicides after 2 minutes feigned, and upper level darkness spells tend to last about 90-100 seconds.<br>Most mobs wont remember you after feign, if there is not still one of your spell effects on them<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
