	   <tr><td colspan=2>"Plus Snare has the added benefit of not wearing off during battle."<br><br>That makes no sense.  Darkness is timed just like snare, so both wear off after its full duration.  Snare is just cheaper to cast than darkness, so it becomes more efficient to recast.  Both have tendencies to resist.  Darkness causes damage, more damage the higher the spell and also has a slower effect the higher the spell.  <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
