<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96661161324107></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96661161324107><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96661161324107>Right click the necrostone</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96661161324107#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=563><span id= >DarkmoonSomberlight</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 11:13 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In big game hunting(dragons, gods, etc) necros function as a mana battery for a cleric.<br><br>The reason for this is that Damage over time spells(DOT) are not usually allowed by the raid leader as the corpse of the creature could in some instances disappear if it dies to a Dot. Direct damage(DD) spells are also not usually wanted as ignite bones(our only true dd) turns the target into a skeleton making it hard for the large number of tanks to keep hacking at it as the small skeleton will get lost in the middle of the 20 tanks and pets beating on it. Especially if there are necro pets attacking as well. This means that we are stuck with our lifetap, which is mana expensive, and does very little damage (338pts). This cuts out a large number of offensive spells.<br><br>However, if you feed all of your mana to a cleric, that cleric will get the ability to cast two extra complete heals, or possibly even three depending on the length of the fight. This comes in handy on those high level warriors and warrior types that have 3-5k hps. If you chain cast your life drain, you will do around 3k damage. The warrior will outdamage you by quite a bit if his life is extended by two/three complete heals. The object is to maximize damage done to the monster as a group, so the best thing for a necro to do in this fight sort of a fight is to feed mana. <br><br>Typical fight:<br>You bum a regen(regrowth is the best), and turn into lich form.<br><br>Leader calls charge. Melee types go in. Pets get sent in. Enchanters debuff, mages debuff, shaman, debuff, you cast the scent line. Fight goes on, nukers start nuking. Depending on how much healing the cleric is doing, you toss in a lifedrain to never have full mana. Optimal is to be around 90% of mana, as lich will replenish the half a bubble very quickly and you do not want to waste mana by not being able to regain mana due to being completely full. Once cleric casts a spell, you essentially start chain casting subversion and feed the cleric. Hopefully, one dead uber mob will result.<br><br>The other function of a necro is if the raid doesn't win. You get to summon the corpses that become unreachable. :)<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
